    "Decisions of a specific nature hold greater relevance to the present concerns or issues end users face.",
    "The provision of global explanations may not sufficiently encompass the contextual factors required for making individual decisions.",
    "End users must comprehend the underlying rationale behind a decision to ascertain its congruence with their expectations, objectives, or principles.",
    "This process facilitates establishing trust and assurance in the system or organization responsible for making the decision.",
    "Providing a comprehensive explanation encompassing all decisions at a global level may result in an excessive amount of information for end users, which can lead to a decrease in their understanding and ability to retain knowledge."
